{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]So I will sing to sleep after the loving
[Dm]With a song I just wrote yesterday
[G7]And I hope you can hear
[C]What the words and the music has to say
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
It's so hard to explain everything that I'm feeling
[Dm]Face to face I just seem to run dry
[G7]But I love you so much
[C]That the sound of your voice can [C7]make me high
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]Thanks for taking [Em]me on a one [G7]way trip to the [C]sun
[Am]And thanks for turning [D7]me into [G7]someone
[C]So I will sing you to sleep after the loving
[Dm]I will brush back the hair from your eyes
[G7]And the smile on your face is so real that it makes me [C]wanna [C7]cry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]And I know that my song is not [E7]saying anything [Am]new
[Dm]Oh but after the loving [G7]I will still be loving [C]you
{end_of_verse}
